Model.Name: Tutorial_3
Model.Description: This tutorial explains how to define arrays of variable values and functions that operate on these arrays, and how to define a non-uniform domain grid.

Object.Name: Q_b
Object.Description: Heat flux at the bottom edge of the plate, W/m2

Object.Name: Q_t
Object.Description: Heat flux at the top edge of the plate, W/m2

Object.Name: c_p
Object.Description: Specific heat capacity of the plate, J/kgK

Object.Name: λ
Object.Description: Thermal conductivity of the plate, W/mK

Object.Name: T_sum
Object.Description: The sum of heat fluxes at the bottom edge of the plate, W/m2

Object.Name: HeatBalance
Object.Description: Heat balance equation. Valid on the open x and y domains

Object.Name: BC_bottom
Object.Description: Boundary conditions for the bottom edge

Object.Name: BC_top
Object.Description: Boundary conditions for the top edge

Object.Name: BC_left
Object.Description: Boundary conditions at the left edge

Object.Name: BC_right
Object.Description: Boundary conditions for the right edge

Object.Name: T_ave
Object.Description: The average temperature of the plate

Object.Name: T_sum
Object.Description: The sum of the plate temperatures
